********************************************************************************
 mcf2graph  : Convert Molecular Coding Format to graphics with MetaPost
 Author     : Akira Yamaji
 version    : 5.30 2026-05-10
 E-mail     : mcf2graph@gmail.com
 Located at : http://www.ctan.org/pkg/mcf2graph
********************************************************************************

1. Introduction
 Molecular Coding Format(MCF) is new linear notation represent
 chemical structure diagrams.
 This Coding is named from programing technique
 such as operator,array,scope,macro,adressing,etc.
 mcf2graph convert from MCF to SVG,PNG,MOL file.
 It is also able to calculate molecular weight,exact mass,molecular formula.

2. The distribution of software
 ( 1) README             This file
 ( 2) CHANGELOG          Changelog file of mcf2graph
 ( 3) mcf_to_graph.cmd   Batch file for compile mcf or mp file
                         drag and drop mcf or mp file on this batch
                          >mcf_to_graph main_lib.mcf
                           create graphic files in ./main_lib-(format)
                          >mcf_to_graph template_lib.mcf
                           create graphic files in ./template_lib-(format)
                          >mcf_to_graph mcf_exa_soc.mp
                           create graphic files in ./mcf_exa_soc-mp
 ( 4) mcf2graph.mp       Main macro of Metapost
 ( 5) main_lib.mcf       Main mcf library file
 ( 6) template_lib.mcf   Template mcf file
 ( 7) mcf_exa_soc.mp     Metapost source example
                         drag and drop this file on mcf_to_graph.cmd
                          >mpost mcf_exa_soc.mp
 ( 8) mcf_manual.tex     MCF syntax manual
                         file (4)(5) must be in the same directory to typeset
 ( 9) mcf_manual.pdf     PDF of (8) typeset with LuaLaTeX
 (10) mcf_example.tex    List of Molecule
                         file (4)(5) must be in the same directory to typeset
 (11) mcf_example.pdf    PDF of (10) typeset with LuaLaTeX

3. Minimum required files to use mcf2graph
 Install texlive or other distribution
 These files are available from texlive2026.iso in the case of texlive
 (1) mpost.exe
   (TeXLive2026/archive/metapost.<os>.r<number>.tar/bin/<os>/mpost.exe)
 (2) mpost.dll
   (TeXLive2026/archive/metapost.<os>.r<number>.tar/bin/<os>/mpost.dll)
 (3) mpost.mp
   (TeXLive2026/archive/metapost.r<number>.tar/texmf-dist/metapost/base/mpost.mp)
 (4) plain.mp
   (TeXLive2026/archive/metapost.r<number>.tar/texmf-dist/metapost/base/plain.mp)

4. Use mcf2graph with MetaPost
     -command line-
 (1) >mcf_to_graph        filename.mcf => output svg,png,mol,report
 (2) >mcf_to_graph        filename.mp  => output svg(default),LV=0(default)
 (3) >mpost               filename.mp  => output svg file
 (4) >mpost -s ahangle=1  filename.mp  => output png file (600dpi)
 (5) >mpost -s ahangle=2  filename.mp  => output png file (1200dpi)
 (6) >mpost -s ahlength=5 filename.mp  => output mol file(V2000)
 (7) >mpost -s ahlength=6 filename.mp  => output mol file(V3000)
 (8) >mpost -s ahlength=7 filename.mp  => output report file

